  "prompt": "What is the meaning of the phrase - 'majboori ka naam mahatma gandhi'?",
  "response": "The phrase \"majboori ka naam Mahatma Gandhi\" is a Hindi expression that translates to \"the name of helplessness (or compulsion) is Mahatma Gandhi.\" It suggests that when people find themselves in a situation of helplessness or compulsion, they may resort to relying on or invoking the name of Mahatma Gandhi, who is widely recognized as a symbol of nonviolent resistance and moral authority.\n\nThis phrase can imply a sense of irony, indicating that sometimes individuals or groups might invoke Gandhi\u2019s ideals even when they are not truly adhering to his principles, or it can highlight the idea that desperate circumstances lead people to turn to revered figures like Gandhi for inspiration. Overall, the phrase reflects the complexities of situations where principles and actions might diverge due to prevailing circumstances.",
